---
description: Error handling rules
globs: ["src/**/*", "src-tauri/src/**/*"]
alwaysApply: true
---

Errors must be explicit, typed, and user-safe.

Rules:
- do not swallow errors
- do not return null/undefined ambiguously for failure cases
- do not rely on console logs as error handling
- convert infrastructure failures into stable app error codes
- preserve technical details internally where useful
- show user-safe error messages in the UI

Frontend:
- every async UI flow must define loading, success, and error behavior
- error UI should provide recovery actions when possible
- destructive actions must surface clear failure messages

Backend:
- raw stderr is not an error contract
- map process failures to typed errors
- include recoverable flag where meaningful
- do not panic for expected runtime failures

Preferred error shape:
- code
- message
- details optional
- recoverable boolean

When in doubt:
- prefer explicit failure over silent fallback